<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
  <!--
  Partial Info.plist — merged into the synthesized Info.plist at build
  time. We use this ONLY for keys that Xcode's INFOPLIST_KEY_*
  synthesis silently drops; every other Info.plist value should stay
  in Config/Shared.xcconfig as INFOPLIST_KEY_* entries.

  Verified-broken keys (Xcode 16, iOS 18):
    - UIBackgroundModes: declared as INFOPLIST_KEY_UIBackgroundModes in
      xcconfig, picked up correctly by xcodebuild -showBuildSettings,
      but never lands in the built app's Info.plist. Without this key
      iOS will not deliver content-available silent pushes — the
      PushStore wiring is otherwise complete (see PushStore.swift,
      AppDelegate.swift, send-push edge function).

  How the merge works:
    Config/Shared.xcconfig still has GENERATE_INFOPLIST_FILE = YES,
    so Xcode synthesises a plist from all the INFOPLIST_KEY_* entries.
    The xcconfig also sets INFOPLIST_FILE = Config/RostrPlus-Info.plist,
    pointing at this file. Xcode reads this file FIRST (as the base
    plist), then layers the synthesised keys on top. Anything in this
    file gets preserved unless an INFOPLIST_KEY_* entry overrides it.

  Keep this file minimal. Every key added here is a key the
  declarative xcconfig path can no longer manage.
  -->
  <key>UIBackgroundModes</key>
  <array>
    <string>remote-notification</string>
  </array>

  <!--
  ITSAppUsesNonExemptEncryption: bake in the export-compliance answer
  so App Store Connect never prompts on a new build. ROSTR+ uses only
  the encryption already in iOS (HTTPS via URLSession, Keychain) and
  bundles no third-party crypto, so the answer is permanently NO —
  this maps to "None of the algorithms mentioned above" in the ASC
  encryption-documentation dialog.

  See https://developer.apple.com/help/app-store-connect/reference/export-compliance-overview

  If a future build ever links a third-party crypto framework (e.g.
  CryptoSwift, libsodium), flip this to <true/> and answer the ASC
  questionnaire about exemption status. Don't just delete this key —
  having no answer at all reopens the manual-dialog loop.
  -->
  <key>ITSAppUsesNonExemptEncryption</key>
  <false/>
</dict>
</plist>
